</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">)</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">However, so</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> few people ride between towns that motorists </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">do not expect to come</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> across a cyclist. </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">The safety of </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">B-roads and ‘minor’ A-roads would </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">improve if</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> more cyclists </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">used</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> them.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">6. </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">Many </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">towns</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> are linked not only by an A- or B-road but also by unc</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">lassified roads. </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">Such</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> roads</span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">tend to be narrow </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">and </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">are </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">slow enough for motor vehicles and bicycles to co-exist </span><span style="font-family:Cambria; font-size:12pt">safely</span><span style="font-family:Camb